<MethodEndpoint

  context={"endpoint"}
>

Deletes a saved asset view so it no longer appears in user view selectors or list endpoints. Use this to clean up deprecated or duplicate views.

**Prerequisites**
1. **viewId** - Obtain from [GET /api/v1.0/assets/views](/docs/api/assets/list-asset-views) before deleting.

**Workflow Example**
1. List views: [GET /api/v1.0/assets/views](/docs/api/assets/list-asset-views) -&gt; identify the view to remove.
2. Delete the view: [DELETE /api/v1.0/assets/views/\{viewId\}](/docs/api/assets/delete-asset-view).

**Minimal Required Fields**: `viewId` (path).
